Package: dgrank
Title: Construct Draper-Gittoes Rankings of Institutions
Version: 1.0
Authors@R: c(person("Daniel", "Helkey", email = "dhelkey@ucsc.edu",
                  role = c("aut", "cre")),
				person("Daniel", "Kirsner", role = "aut"),
				person("David", "Draper", role = "ctb"),
				person("Jessica", "Liu", role = "ctb"))
Description: Provides functions for ranking institions with respect to binary outcome performance. 
    Rankings are computed according to Draper-Gittoes (2004) methodology. Functions are provided
		to generate composite scores. Main function intended for CPQCC/VON usage, but fast functions are
		provided for Bayesian linear and probit regression.
Depends: R (>= 3.1.0)
License: MIT + file LICENSE
LazyData: true
Imports:
    Matrix,
    truncnorm,
  	methods
Suggests:
	ggplot2,
    testthat,
	MASS,
	sas7bdat
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
